    "body": "It's currently not possible to tell the compiler that a given (parallel) loop can be vectorized/SIMD'ized. \r\nWe'd like to have a way to annotate pranges in a way that tells the compiler to vectorize the loop.\r\n\r\nCython uses OpenMP for its prange construct. OpenMP comes with a SIMD directive which does exactly that. When adding the `SIMD` to what cython generates for the following code, icc generates vectorized code which is then almost Vector-length/32 times faster:\r\n\r\n```\r\n@boundscheck(False)\r\n@wraparound(False)\r\n@cdivision(True)\r\n@initializedcheck(False)\r\ndef black_scholes_par(int nopt,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float[::1] price,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float[::1] strike,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float[::1] t,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float rate,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float vol,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float[::1] call,\r\n\t\t\t\t  float[::1] put):\r\n    # using [::1] is essential for autovectorization\r\n\tcdef int i\r\n\tcdef float P, S, a, b, z, c, Se, y, T\r\n\tcdef float d1, d2, w1, w2\r\n\tcdef float mr = -rate\r\n\tcdef float sig_sig_two = vol * vol * 2\r\n\r\n    # In order to release the GIL for a parallel loop, code in the with block cannot\r\n    # manipulate Python objects in any way.\r\n\twith nogil, parallel():\r\n\t\tfor i in prange(nopt):\r\n\t\t\tP = price [i]\r\n\t\t\tS = strike [i]\r\n\t\t\tT = t [i]\r\n\r\n\t\t\ta = log(P / S)\r\n\t\t\tb = T * mr\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tz = T * sig_sig_two\r\n\t\t\tc = 0.25 * z\r\n\t\t\ty = 1./sqrt(z)\r\n\r\n\t\t\tw1 = (a - b + c) * y\r\n\t\t\tw2 = (a - b - c) * y\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\td1 = 0.5 + 0.5 * erf(w1)\r\n\t\t\td2 = 0.5 + 0.5 * erf(w2)\r\n\r\n\t\t\tSe = exp(b) * S\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tcall [i] = P * d1 - Se * d2\r\n\t\t\tput [i] = call [i] - P + Se\r\n```\r\n\r\nI suggest adding a boolean flag `simd=[False|True]` to `prange`.\r\n",
